From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 11:55:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] compat: fix build with kernel 3.10

Kernel 3.10 exposes device_caps in struct v4l2_capability, but not in
struct video_device yet. Guard the assignment so older kernels only touch
the userspace capability struct.
---
 v4l2loopback.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/v4l2loopback.c b/v4l2loopback.c
index cee4eec..4eb1b2e 100644
--- a/v4l2loopback.c
+++ b/v4l2loopback.c
@@ -698,7 +698,11 @@ static int vidioc_querycap(struct file *file, void *fh, struct v4l2_capability *
 		}
 	}
 
-	dev->vdev->device_caps = cap->device_caps = cap->capabilities = capabilities;
+	cap->capabilities = capabilities;
+	cap->device_caps = capabilities;
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(4, 0, 0)
+	dev->vdev->device_caps = capabilities;
+#endif
 
 #if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(3, 3, 0)
 	cap->capabilities |= V4L2_CAP_DEVICE_CAPS;
-- 
2.49.0
